1. Who are the specific individuals or groups that considered "The Last Jedi" the best Star Wars film since "The Empire Strikes Back"?
2. What criteria or reasons did those individuals or groups provide to support the claim that "The Last Jedi" is one of the best Star Wars films?
3. How has the anticipation or marketing for "Star Wars: Episode IX" contributed to the statement that it is provisionally scheduled for release on December 20, 2019?
4. Can you provide evidence or statements from reliable sources confirming the claim that "The Last Jedi" is considered by some as the best Star Wars film since "The Empire Strikes Back"?
